name: Qantas A330 Business Class - Welcome Home!
description:
This was my 12th flight at the end of a very busy 25 day work trip to Europe and Morocco - I was ready to come home!  Luckily Qantas delivered the goods in their wonderful new business class seats on the A330 as I flew from Osaka Japan to Sydney Australia.

This Qantas business class flight review covers the Sakura business class lounge at Kansai Airport, boarding, taxi, take off and the great friendly onboard service from the Qantas crew.  I also cover the business class menu, the in-flight meals, the amenities kit and the famous Qantas inflight PJs.   This business class flight review also covers the new Qantas business class seat on the Airbus A330 which converts into a fully flat bed.  I also cover the landing in Sydney and some great footage of the Queen of the Skies - a the graceful Qantas Boeing 747-400 which landed just behind us.   

For more flight reviews please check out my channel or the links at the bottom of this description.  

Route:    Kansai Osaka, Japan (KIX) to Sydney, Australia (SYD)
Length:  4,841 miles,  9:50 hrs
Flight:     QF34
When:    April 2018
Aircraft:  Airbus A330-303   registration VH-QPJ - 2006, 12 years
Seat:       3A
Camera:  Sony FDR-AXP53
